{
  "id": "019cdda6-8f82-7973-ae5f-73efa8b864ea",
  "content": "# Playwright MCP Pitfalls and Workarounds\n\nErrors encountered during visual content production, with fixes:\n\n1. **file:// URLs blocked** — Playwright MCP security policy blocks file:// protocol. Fix: serve files via HTTP server from workspace root (`python3 -m http.server 8099 --bind 127.0.0.1`).\n\n2. **HTTP server 404s** — Server started from subdirectory causes URL path mismatches. Fix: always start from workspace root so URL paths match repo-relative file paths.\n\n3. **Browser version mismatch** — Devcontainer may have older Chromium or none cached. Fix: `npx playwright install chromium` before rendering.\n\n4. **`require` not available in browser_run_code** — Playwright MCP's `browser_run_code` executes inside browser context (no Node.js APIs). Fix: use standalone Node.js scripts for rendering, not `browser_run_code`.\n\n5. **Playwright evaluate() max args** — `page.evaluate()` only accepts one argument. Fix: wrap multiple parameters in a single object: `page.evaluate(({ a, b }) => ..., { a, b })`.\n\n6. **flex-grow spacers trigger false height failures** — Empty flex-grow divs expand to fill remaining space, appearing to exceed content budget. Fix: skip elements with `flex-grow != 0` and empty text in height calculations.",
  "source_version": "mcp",
  "scope_id": "corvia",
  "workstream": "main",
